I consent to my Fitness to Work assessment and associated relevant documentation being released to my  prospective employer and the Client or Company nominated Doctor and Health Team.
By signing below, I confirm I understand that:

• The purpose of gathering this medical information is to enable medical personnel to determine my fitness  to work offshore and in the context of the Client’s Offshore Policies and Procedures. The information will  also serve as a medical record for health professionals providing medical services offshore.

• The data will be handled confidentially at all times and in accordance with the Privacy Act (1988) and  related Australian Privacy Principles. It will be kept on an electronic medical record database in Australia or  on the Client’s system. The latter is an electronic medical record database used by the Client to store  confidential medical data on and is stored centrally. Any information stored in either electronic medical  record databases; the local Australian or the Client’s systems, is available only to the Client’s Health Staff,  Nominated Doctors and Medics.

• I may be contacted directly by my prospective employer, the Client’s Nominated Doctor or Health Team to  discuss aspects of my assessment. In order to make a fitness for work determination, I may be requested  to supply additional information.
• The final decision on my fitness for work rests with the Client’s Nominated Doctor or Health Team.
• Failure to provide consent means I will not be able to be mobilised onto offshore or remote facilities under  the Client’s Operated Control.
• I may at any time request to view my medical record in order to correct or update information; such a  request must be made in writing to the Client’s Health Team.
• I acknowledge that the Client’s facilities are non-smoking
• I acknowledge that the body weight limit for the Client is 135 kg
